[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer fuzzing run triggered a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception indicating[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man OS command injection vulnerability in the Apache Tika-based code path. The [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitizer detected untrusted input flowing into a `ProcessBuilder.start` call, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mraising the risk of remote code execution when the application invokes external [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshell commands.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue: During a Jazzer fuzz test, the `OsCommandInjection` sanitizer intercepted [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma call to `ProcessBuilder.start`, throwing a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: OS [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCommand Injection` exception.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Type: OS Command Injection – executing operating-system commands [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith attacker-controlled data can enable arbitrary command execution on the host.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack Trace Highlights:  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `OsCommandInjection.processImplStartHook` flagged the risky call.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The sink originates in `java.lang.ProcessBuilder.start`, invoked by [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.utils.ProcessUtils.execute`.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The vulnerable call chain proceeds through Tika’s `ShellCodeDetector.detect` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand on to high-level parsers and the TikaCLI entry point.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m exercises TikaCLI, but the root [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39missue lies in how Tika invokes external commands.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important Observations:  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The sanitizer identifies untrusted data reaching the `ProcessBuilder` API.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Multiple layers of Apache Tika processing [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdetect, parse, CLI[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m culminate in the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The harness merely triggers the code path; it is not the source of the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Areas for Investigation:  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • ProcessUtils.execute [0m[1;39m([0m[39mshell invocation logic[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • ShellCodeDetector.detect [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommand construction and input handling[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • CompositeDetector and higher-level parser classes that call into [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mShellCodeDetector  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • TikaCLI’s integration points where parsed or detected content is forwarded to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexternal processes  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Any code that builds command strings or argument lists from untrusted input [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore invoking `ProcessBuilder`[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mFiles.copy[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtis.getPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, tmpFile, StandardCopyOption.REPLACE_EXISTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m:        ProcessBuilder pb = new [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfileName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m101[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mpb.directory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtmpDir.toFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m102[0m[39m:        try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m:            FileProcessResult result = [0m[1;35mProcessUtils.execute[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpb, [0m[1;36m20000[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m100000[0m[39m, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100000[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m104[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mresult.getExitValue[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSHELL_NO_ARGS, true[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/detect/FileCommandDetector.jav[0m[1;92ma:121[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m126[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m121[0m[39m:        String[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m args =[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m122[0m[39m:                new String[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m{[0m[1;35mProcessUtils.escapeCommandLine[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfileCommandPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"-b"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"--mime-type"[0m[39m,[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m123[0m[39m:                        [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mProcessUtils.escapeCommandLine[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mpath.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m124[0m[39m:        ProcessBuilder builder = new [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39margs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m125[0m[39m:        FileProcessResult result = [0m[1;35mProcessUtils.execute[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuilder, timeoutMs, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m10000[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m10000[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m126[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mresult.isTimeout[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The root cause is that two Tika detectors—ShellCodeDetector and [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFileCommandDetector—invoke external processes via ProcessBuilder.start, triggering [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJazzer’s OS command injection sanitizer. To resolve this without altering fuzz [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness or external libs, we must eliminate these internal ProcessBuilder calls and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreplace them with equivalent pure-Java logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor safe whitelisting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m so that no [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muntrusted data reaches a shell/exec sink.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Preserve Core Logic  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - ShellCodeDetector must still detect shell scripts or code fragments in input [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstreams.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - FileCommandDetector must still extract a file’s MIME type accurately [0m[1;39m([0m[39mits [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcurrent behavior is “run `file -b --mime-type <path>`”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Strategy Steps  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Remove External Execution from ShellCodeDetector  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Rename the existing method `[0m[1;35mdetect[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath tmpFile, Metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor inline it[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto a new private method, e.g. `boolean [0m[1;35misShellScript[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath tmpFile[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. In `isShellScript`: open the file, read the first few bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. up to [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to check for a shebang [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“#!”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. If present, return true.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Optionally, for improved accuracy, scan the first [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m KB of content for [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcommon shell keywords [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. “function”, “do”, “done”, “fi”, “declare”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. In `[0m[1;35mShellCodeDetector.detect[0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream, Metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         – After writing the temp file, invoke `[0m[1;35misShellScript[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmpFile[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         – If `true`, set `SHELL_NO_ARGS` metadata and return the detected type; [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39melse return OCTET_STREAM [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor let the next detector process[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Drop `new [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and the call to `ProcessUtils.execute` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentirely.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Replace FileCommandDetector’s External “file” Command  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Leverage Tika’s built-in magic-database detection: call [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.mime.MagicDetector` or `org.apache.tika.mime.MagicMime` APIs to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetect the MIME type from the file path or byte array.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Remove the block that builds `String[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m args = [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[32m"file"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"-b"[0m[39m, [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"--mime-type"[0m[39m, <path> [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` and the calls to `ProcessBuilder` + [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ProcessUtils.execute`.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. After spooling/copying to a temp path, load the file bytes or pass the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Path` to the MagicDetector’s Java API, retrieve the MIME string, and set metadata [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjust as before [0m[1;39m([0m[39mhonoring `useMime` flag[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Preserve the existing configuration properties [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtimeoutMs, maxBytes, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39museMime, fileCommandPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but mark `fileCommandPath` deprecated [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno-op[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or remove [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min a later version.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Update CompositeDetector  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - No changes needed: ShellCodeDetector and FileCommandDetector remain [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregistered, but their implementations no longer execute external processes.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Backward Compatibility & Configuration  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Introduce a feature flag or config parameter [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. `tika.config [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<detector>.useExternalExec = true/false`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m defaulting to `false`.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - If `true`, fall back to the old external command logic—guarded behind an [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexplicit opt-in so that users who rely on `[0m[35m/usr/bin/[0m[95mfile[0m[39m` can restore legacy [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Tests for legacy behavior should be updated to run only when this flag is [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mset.  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By moving both detectors to pure-Java detection, no untrusted data flows into [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ProcessBuilder`, eliminating the sanitizer finding.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Core detection functionality is preserved or improved [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmagic-DB covers more [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignatures than `file`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No harness, fuzzing logic, or external dependencies are modified; we only [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtouch Tika’s own source.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Broad utility functions [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ProcessUtils`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remain untouched, avoiding unintended[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mside effects elsewhere.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigation  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Slight differences in MIME identification: magic-DB might classify some [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39medge-cases differently than the system `file` utility. Mitigate by verifying key [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfile types in Tika’s test suite and adjusting magic definitions if needed.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Shell code detection via shebang+keyword scan may be less comprehensive than [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecuting the script, but truly executing user scripts on the host is a security [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39manti-pattern. If deeper shell detection is needed, consider a sandboxed subprocess [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor bytecode-level parser in a later release.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. References & Precedents  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Tika’s existing MagicDetector implementation is pure-Java and used elsewhere [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g. org.apache.tika.detect.MagicDetector[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Other parsers [0m[1;39m([0m[39mPDF, Office[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m do not spawn external tools but rely on Java [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibraries—this change aligns shell and file detection with that model.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. No Harness or Test Code Changes  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing tests should pass unchanged—or in the case of integration tests [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpecting external commands, they can be gated by the new `useExternalExec` flag.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No modifications to fuzz harness or external libraries.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>tika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/detect/ShellCodeDetector.jav[0m[1;92ma:9[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m8[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m106[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>tika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/detect/FileCommandDetector.jav[0m[1;92ma[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m:121[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m126[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         An OS-command-injection finding was raised by Jazzer when the fuzzer exercised      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Apache Tika’s ShellCodeDetector, which uses `ProcessBuilder` [1m([0mvia                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ProcessUtils.execute`[1m)[0m to invoke external commands. A proposed patch removed the   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         external command invocation in both ShellCodeDetector and                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         FileCommandDetector—replacing it with a simple shebang check and the built-in Tika  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         magic database, respectively. After applying the patch, the Tika core module fails  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         to compile due to malformed `try`[35m/[0m`finally` blocks and mismatched braces in         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ShellCodeDetector.java`.                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Initial Issue                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Jazzer reported `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: OS Command Injection` rooted in a   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         call to `ProcessBuilder.start`.                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Stack trace points to `[1;35morg.apache.tika.detect.ShellCodeDetector.detect[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m`      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         which copies the input to a temp file and then executes it via                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mProcessUtils.execute[0m[1m([0mpb, [33m...[0m[1m)[0m`.                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The harness [1m([0m`TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer`[1m)[0m invoked the Tika CLI, which in turn         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         triggers `ShellCodeDetector`, leading to the exception.                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Important Observations                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The vulnerability arises from executing potentially untrusted input as an         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         external process.                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The fuzzer’s crash input demonstrates the code path but is not the root cause—it  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         merely drives execution into Tika’s detection logic.                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Two detector classes are impacted:                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • ShellCodeDetector – executes a temp file via `ProcessBuilder`.                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • FileCommandDetector – invokes the external `file` command.                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch Attempt                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **ShellCodeDetector.java**                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Removed construction of `ProcessBuilder pb` and the external execution call.   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Inserted inline shebang check: open the temp file, read the first two bytes,   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         set metadata if `#!` is found.                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Intended to wrap the shebang logic in a `try [1m{[0m … [1m}[0m finally [1m{[0m delete temp dir   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m}[0m` block.                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **FileCommandDetector.java**                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Removed invocation of the external `file` command [1m([0m`ProcessUtils.execute`[1m)[0m.    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Switched to Tika’s built-in `[1;35mMimeTypes.getDefaultMimeTypes[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m[1;35m.detect[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m`.     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Log After Applying Patch                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Compilation fails in `ShellCodeDetector.java` with seven errors:                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m1[0m. “‘try’ without ‘catch’, ‘finally’ or resource declarations”                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m2[0m. “illegal start of type” at several lines                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m3[0m. “[1m<[0m[1;95midentifier[0m[39m> expected”  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. “class, interface, enum, or record expected”  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExcerpt of faulty region [0m[1;39m([0m[39mapproximate line numbers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33m...[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPath tmpDir = [0m[1;35mFiles.createTempDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcwd, [0m[32m"tika-shell-detect-"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Missing code that opens a try block?[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    Path tmpFile = [0m[1;35mtmpDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfileName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mFiles.copy[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtis.getPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, tmpFile, StandardCopyOption.REPLACE_EXISTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Inline shell script detection[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    boolean isShell = false;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream fis = [0m[1;35mFiles.newInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmpFile[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[33m...[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39misShell[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSHELL_NO_ARGS, true[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m finally block is no longer matched with a preceding try[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfinally [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mFileUtils.deleteDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtmpDir.toFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33m...[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis misalignment between `try`, block braces, and `finally` generates the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation errors listed above.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **[0m[1;35mShellCodeDetector.detect[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: verify the correct placement and pairing of [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`try` and `finally` blocks, ensure braces match, and restore any required exception[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandling or resource-management structure.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Overall temp-file lifecycle**: confirm deletion logic remains in a valid [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`finally` clause or try-with-resources.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **[0m[1;35mFileCommandDetector.detectOnPath[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: check that the new MIME-type detector [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintegration compiles and behaves as intended.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **ProcessUtils and ExternalParser integration points**: ensure no residual [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvocations of external processes that could trigger similar issues.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m141[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmt == null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m143[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m144[0m[39m:                return mt;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m145[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m146[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m147[0m[39m:        return MediaType.OCTET_STREAM;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m148[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. ShellCodeDetector.java – Restore correct try/finally block pairing and replace [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexternal exec with inline shebang sniff:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Remove imports for ProcessBuilder, ProcessUtils, FileProcessResult.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. After creating `tmpDir`, start a `try [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m finally [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mFileUtils.deleteDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtmpDir.toFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` block:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Inside `try`, resolve and copy the temp file.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Perform shebang detection via a nested try-with-resources on [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mFiles.newInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmpFile[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         boolean isShell = false;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream fis = [0m[1;35mFiles.newInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmpFile[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m header = new byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mfis.read[0m[1;39m([0m[39mheader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m && header[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'#'[0m[39m && header[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'!'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 isShell = true;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39misShell[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSHELL_NO_ARGS, true[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Exit the `try`, enter the `finally` to delete `tmpDir`.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. After the finally block, return `SHELL_SCRIPT` unconditionally [0m[1;39m([0m[39msame as [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginal[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Ensure braces are balanced: one `try [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m finally [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` and then a single [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`return`.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. FileCommandDetector.java – Replace external [0m[32m'file'[0m[39m command with Tika’s built-in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMIME detection:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Remove imports: `ProcessUtils`, `FileProcessResult`, and `StringUtils`.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Add import: `org.apache.tika.mime.MimeTypes`.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. In `[0m[1;35mdetectOnPath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath path, Metadata metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Remove the `ProcessBuilder` construction and `ProcessUtils.execute` block [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m121[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m126[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Replace with:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        MimeTypes mimeTypes = [0m[1;35mMimeTypes.getDefaultMimeTypes[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        MediaType mt = [0m[1;35mmimeTypes.detect[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath, metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        String mimeString = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmt != null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ? [0m[1;35mmt.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m : null;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmimeString == null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return MediaType.OCTET_STREAM;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFILE_MIME, mimeString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39museMime[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return mt;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return MediaType.OCTET_STREAM;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Preserve existing `throws IOException`, input-reset logic, and `useMime` flag[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msemantics.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Testing & Validation:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compile `tika-core` to verify no syntax or brace-structure errors.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run unit tests for both detectors to ensure:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • ShellCodeDetector still detects scripts by shebang and sets `sh:no_args`.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Non-shell inputs yield `MediaType.OCTET_STREAM`.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • FileCommandDetector returns the same MIME types for known files.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzer harness remains unmodified and should exercise these code paths without[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvoking any external processes.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Restoring the outer try/finally around the temp-directory operations preserves [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup semantics while removing unsafe external execution.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Inline shebang detection is minimal, safe, and matches existing “firstBytes” [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Leveraging `[0m[1;35mMimeTypes.getDefaultMimeTypes[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.detect[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in FileCommandDetector [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreuses Tika’s built-in magic database, eliminating the OS‐call vulnerability [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout regressing detect-on-path behavior.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Braces and return placement mirror patterns seen in the original code [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginal try/finally + return[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and in other detectors [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., MagicDetector[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensuring compile‐time correctness.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No modifications to harness, fuzzing logic, or external dependencies are [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrequired, preserving existing tests and CI workflows.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                 at                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mTikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:54[0m[1m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: d7514645016ef7a8                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The fuzzer raised a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` for OS command injection in two   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         detectors of the Apache Tika codebase—`ShellCodeDetector` and                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `FileCommandDetector`—that invoke external processes via `ProcessBuilder` and       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ProcessUtils.execute`. A proposed patch removed all external process invocation:   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - In `ShellCodeDetector`, it commented out the use of                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ProcessBuilder`[35m/[0m`ProcessUtils` and added a simple shebang‐based header check.      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - In `FileCommandDetector`, it replaced the call to the Linux `file` command with   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Tika’s `[1;35mMimeTypes.detect[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m`.                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         After applying the patch, the build failed with a compilation error in              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `FileCommandDetector.java`, specifically an “incompatible types: java.nio.file.Path [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         cannot be converted to java.io.InputStream” at the call to `[1;35mmimeTypes.detect[0m[1m([0mpath,  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         metadata[1m)[0m`.                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Initial Issue                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - A Jazzer fuzzing run detected an OS command injection vulnerability when Tika     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         invoked external commands [1m([0m`ProcessBuilder.start`[1m)[0m with attacker‐controlled file    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         paths.                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The stack trace points to `org.apache.tika.detect.ShellCodeDetector` calling      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mProcessUtils.execute[0m[1m([0mpb, [33m...[0m[1m)[0m`, and similarly to                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.tika.detect.FileCommandDetector` running the `file` utility.            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The critical finding is that user‐supplied data can end up as arguments to an OS  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         command, enabling remote code execution.                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch Attempt                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - In `ShellCodeDetector.java`:                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • Commented out imports for `FileProcessResult` and `ProcessUtils`.               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • Removed use of `ProcessBuilder` to execute the file.                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • Added logic to copy the input stream to a temp file, read the first two bytes,  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         and if they match `#!`, mark the file as a shell script.                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - In `FileCommandDetector.java`:                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • Removed imports and calls to `FileProcessResult`, `ProcessUtils`, and utility   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         methods.                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • Introduced `[1;35mMimeTypes.getDefaultMimeTypes[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` and replaced the external `file`   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         command with `[1;35mmimeTypes.detect[0m[1m([0mpath, metadata[1m)[0m`.                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • Simplified the return of `MediaType` based on the `MimeTypes` API result.       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch Result                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - During compilation of `FileCommandDetector.java`, Maven reported:                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           “incompatible types: java.nio.file.Path cannot be converted to                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         java.io.InputStream” at the line calling `[1;35mmimeTypes.detect[0m[1m([0mpath, metadata[1m)[0m`.        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - This indicates that the `detect` method in `MimeTypes` does not accept a `Path`   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         directly, but rather expects an `InputStream` [1m([0mor similar[1m)[0m, causing the type        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         mismatch.                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Areas for Further Investigation                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The API signature of `[1;35morg.apache.tika.mime.MimeTypes.detect[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m`—verify what     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         parameters it accepts and whether there is an overload for `Path`.                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Usage of `ProcessUtils` and `FileProcessResult` across the codebase to assess     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         where external commands remain.                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Consistency between `ShellCodeDetector` and `FileCommandDetector` approaches to   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         detection: investigate other detectors or parsers invoking processes.               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The temp‐file handling and resource cleanup patterns introduced in                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ShellCodeDetector`—ensure they align with existing conventions.                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m<[0m[1;95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
