[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A Jazzer fuzzing session of Apache Tika triggered a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical`   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         for OS command injection. The stack trace shows that untrusted input flows into a   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ProcessBuilder` invocation in `ProcessUtils.execute`, ultimately in                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ShellCodeDetector.detect`. A proposed patch replaces the use of the external       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         “file” command in `FileCommandDetector` with a pure‐Java MIME detection via         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `MimeTypes.detect`. After applying that patch, the same OS command injection        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         exception still occurs—indicating the root call site [1m([0m`ShellCodeDetector`[1m)[0m remains  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         unmodified.                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Initial Issue                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Jazzer reported an OS command injection vulnerability                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: OS Command          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Injection`[1m)[0m.                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The crash originates in `ProcessBuilder.start`, called by `ProcessUtils.execute`, [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         invoked by `ShellCodeDetector.detect`.                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The chain is:                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           ShellCodeDetector.detect → CompositeDetector.detect → TikaCLI →                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer → fuzzer harness.                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The harness passes attacker-controlled data to Tika’s detectors, ultimately       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         leading to an unsafe external command execution.                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Important Observations                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The vulnerable call site is in `org.apache.tika.utils.ProcessUtils.execute`,      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         which wraps `ProcessBuilder` to run OS commands.                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The exception occurs specifically in `ShellCodeDetector`, not in                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `FileCommandDetector`.                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The metadata and mime-type detection logic in other detectors [1m([0me.g.,              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `FileCommandDetector`[1m)[0m also invoke external commands via `ProcessUtils`.            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch Attempt                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Modified                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `tika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/detect/FileCommandDetector.java`.          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • Removed imports and usages of `ProcessUtils`, `FileProcessResult`, and          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `StringUtils`.                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • Introduced `[1;35mMimeTypes.getDefaultMimeTypes[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m[1;35m.detect[0m[1m([0mInputStream, Metadata[1m)[0m` to   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         perform in-process detection.                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • Replaced the external “file” command invocation with Java stream-based          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         detection via `[1;35mFiles.newInputStream[0m[1m([0mpath[1m)[0m`.                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The diff edits only affect `[1;35mFileCommandDetector.detectOnPath[0m[1m([0mPath, Metadata[1m)[0m`. No [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         changes were made to `ShellCodeDetector` or `ProcessUtils`.                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Result After Patch                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The same Jazzer exception stack trace appears, still pointing at                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ProcessUtils.execute` and `ShellCodeDetector.detect`.                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The log after patch is identical to pre-patch, confirming the unaddressed         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         vulnerability remains in `ShellCodeDetector`.                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Areas for Further Investigation                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - `org.apache.tika.detect.ShellCodeDetector` – this is the actual caller of         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ProcessUtils.execute` in the failure stack.                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Other detectors in `org.apache.tika.detect` or `org.apache.tika.parser.external`  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         that invoke external processes via `ProcessBuilder`[35m/[0m`ProcessUtils`.                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Review the implementation of `ProcessUtils` itself to identify all entry points   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         that invoke system commands.                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Audit any CLI entry points [1m([0me.g., `TikaCLI`[1m)[0m that might rely on detectors         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         spawning external processes.                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m<[0m[1;95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== Java Exception: com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: OS[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCommand Injection[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mFiles.copy[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtis.getPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, tmpFile, StandardCopyOption.REPLACE_EXISTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m:        ProcessBuilder pb = new [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfileName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m101[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mpb.directory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtmpDir.toFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m102[0m[39m:        try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m:            FileProcessResult result = [0m[1;35mProcessUtils.execute[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpb, [0m[1;36m20000[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m100000[0m[39m, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100000[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m104[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mresult.getExitValue[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSHELL_NO_ARGS, true[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m finally [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mFileUtils.deleteDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtmpDir.toFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:        return SHELL_SCRIPT;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/utils/ProcessUtils.jav[0m[1;92ma:87[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m96[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m:    public static FileProcessResult [0m[1;35mexecute[0m[1;39m([0m[39mProcessBuilder pb,[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:                                            long timeoutMillis,[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:                                            int maxStdoutBuffer, int [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaxStdErrBuffer[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m90[0m[39m:            throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m91[0m[39m:        Process p = null;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m92[0m[39m:        String id = null;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m93[0m[39m:        try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m94[0m[39m:            p = [0m[1;35mpb.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m95[0m[39m:            id = [0m[1;35mregister[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m96[0m[39m:            long elapsed = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/utils/ProcessUtils.jav[0m[1;92ma:108[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m115[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:            try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:                complete = [0m[1;35mp.waitFor[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtimeoutMillis, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:                elapsed = [0m[1;35mSystem.currentTimeMillis[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - start;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m111[0m[39m:                if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcomplete[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m112[0m[39m:                    exitValue = [0m[1;35mp.exitValue[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m113[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;35moutThread.join[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1000[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m114[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;35merrThread.join[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1000[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m115[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview and Root-Cause Analysis  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The vulnerability originates in [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35morg.apache.tika.detect.ShellCodeDetector.detect[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which unconditionally [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrites untrusted bytes to a temp file and invokes it via [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mProcessUtils.execute[0m[1;39m([0m[39mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. This is an OS‐command injection vector [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbecause attacker-controlled content is executed by the shell.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Previous patches correctly replaced external invocation in [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FileCommandDetector` but left the dangerous call in `ShellCodeDetector` untouched.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Core Insight and Required Preservation  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must remove or neutralize the external execution in [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ShellCodeDetector.detect` without breaking Tika’s overall detection pipeline.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `ShellCodeDetector` exists to recognize shell scripts; its only purpose is to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmark a resource as `SHELL_SCRIPT` when appropriate.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other existing functionality [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparsing, metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m depends on actually [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecuting the script; they only check the exit code to set the `SHELL_NO_ARGS` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflag, which downstream components rarely use.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. High-Level Patch Plan  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Refactor `ShellCodeDetector.detect` to use pure-Java inspection:  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Drop all code that:  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         – Creates a temporary directory and copies the input file.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         – Builds and executes a `ProcessBuilder`.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         – Invokes `ProcessUtils.execute`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`FileProcessResult`.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Replace with a lightweight content check on the script file:  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         – If the `TikaInputStream` has an associated `Path`, open it with [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mFiles.newBufferedReader[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         – Read the first line; if it starts with `#!` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mshebang[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, treat it as a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshell script.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         – Optionally, also check common file extensions [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `.sh`, `.bash`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m if [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdesired.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         – If a shebang is detected, set `[0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSHELL_NO_ARGS, false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39momit setting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and return `SHELL_SCRIPT`.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         – Otherwise, return `MediaType.OCTET_STREAM` so that other detectors can [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrun.  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Clean up imports: remove `ProcessUtils`, `FileProcessResult`, `StringUtils`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FileUtils`, and `Paths`, `Files.createTempDirectory`, `ProcessBuilder`, etc., that[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare no longer needed.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Preserve existing API will-return and metadata keys:  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – The signature and return type of `[0m[1;35mdetect[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` remain unchanged.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – Consumers of `SHELL_NO_ARGS` will see `false` or absence; tests which [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39massert only the presence of `SHELL_SCRIPT` should still pass.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Detailed Steps  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Open `tika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/detect/ShellCodeDetector.java`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Locate the `[0m[1;35mdetect[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m[1;36m90[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m110[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Remove the following block in its entirety:  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – Lines that create `tmpDir`, copy the file, build and start [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ProcessBuilder`, call `[0m[1;35mProcessUtils.execute[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, check `[0m[1;35mresult.getExitValue[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand finally delete the directory.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Insert in its place a pure-Java shebang check:  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Check `[0m[1;35mTikaInputStream.getPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m != null`; if null, immediately return [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MediaType.OCTET_STREAM`.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Use `[0m[1;35mFiles.newBufferedReader[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath, StandardCharsets.UTF_8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to read the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfirst line [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwith `[0m[1;35m.readLine[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • If the line is non-null and starts with `#!`, set the metadata key [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`SHELL_NO_ARGS` to `false` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor do not set it[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, then `return SHELL_SCRIPT;`.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Else, return `MediaType.OCTET_STREAM`.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Remove now-unused imports: `org.apache.tika.utils.ProcessUtils`, [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.utils.FileProcessResult`, `org.apache.tika.utils.StringUtils`, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.commons.io.FileUtils` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor similar[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and any `java.nio.file.Paths`, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ProcessBuilder`, etc.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. Run the full test suite to ensure no regressions in other detectors or [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsers.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification and Side-Effect Analysis  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By eliminating the runtime execution of untrusted scripts, the OS command [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minjection vector is fully closed.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The new detection logic is purely content-based [0m[1;39m([0m[39mshebang + optional [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextension[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which is sufficient for identifying shell scripts.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We preserve the method signature and the `SHELL_SCRIPT` return type, so no [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdownstream code or tests should break.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We may lose the semantic of “scripts that run without arguments return zero [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexit code,” but that flag was not critical to core functionality; setting it to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`false` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor omitting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is safe.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This patch does not alter any fuzzing harness or external dependencies, so [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting fuzz targets and tests remain valid.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Related Detectors  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A quick audit of other detectors [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., in `org.apache.tika.parser.external`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshowed no other direct use of `ProcessUtils.execute` on attacker-controlled content[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the detection phase. If future audits reveal additional cases, apply the same [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. No Harness-Code or Test-Code Changes  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This patch strictly modifies only the production code in `ShellCodeDetector`. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFuzz harnesses, tests, and external libraries remain untouched.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We satisfy the requirement to reapply previous patches [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthey were in [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FileCommandDetector`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and now fully address the root cause in [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ShellCodeDetector`.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The codebase was flagged by Jazzer with a FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical error for OS  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         command injection in `ShellCodeDetector`, where a shell script file is copied to a  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         temporary directory and executed via `ProcessBuilder` [35m/[0m `ProcessUtils.execute`. In  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         response, a patch was attempted that removes the external process invocation and    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         instead opens the file directly with `Files.newBufferedReader`, checking its first  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         line for a shebang [1m([0m`#!`[1m)[0m. After applying this patch, the build fails in            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `tika-core` with a compilation error:                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         “cannot find symbol: variable StringUtils” in `ShellCodeDetector.java`.             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Exception:                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: OS Command       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Injection                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Stack trace highlights `[1;35mShellCodeDetector.detect[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` invoking                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `[1;35mProcessUtils.execute[0m[1m([0mProcessBuilder, [33m...[0m[1m)[0m` on an attacker-controlled file,    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         which can lead to remote code execution.                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Key Observations from the Initial Issue                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The detector creates a temporary directory under the current working           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         directory.                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - It copies the target file into that directory, then runs it [1m([0mno arguments[1m)[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         with `ProcessBuilder`.                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - `[1;35mProcessUtils.execute[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` applies timeouts and resource limits but still     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         executes untrusted data.                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Jazzer flags this as a critical security issue [1m([0mOS command injection[1m)[0m.         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Removed imports:                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `org.apache.tika.utils.FileProcessResult`,                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `org.apache.tika.utils.ProcessUtils`,                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `org.apache.tika.utils.StringUtils`                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Added imports:                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `java.io.BufferedReader`,                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets`,                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `java.nio.file.Files`                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Deleted code that:                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Created a temp directory and file copy                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Built and executed a `ProcessBuilder`                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Called `[1;35mProcessUtils.execute[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m`                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Deleted the temp directory                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Added code that:                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Retrieves the original file path from `TikaInputStream`                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Opens a `BufferedReader` on the file in UTF-[1;36m8[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Reads the first line and checks whether it starts with `#!`                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Returns `SHELL_SCRIPT` if it does, otherwise `MediaType.OCTET_STREAM`        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Patch Result and Build Log                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Maven compilation fails in `tika-core` with:                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `[35m/org/apache/tika/detect/[0m[95mShellCodeDetector.java[0m:[1m[[0m[1;36m84[0m,[1;36m13[0m[1m][0m cannot find symbol     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m               symbol: variable StringUtils`                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - This indicates that after removing the import for `StringUtils`, there remains [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         at least one reference to it in the code [1m([0mlikely in methods not updated by the      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         patch[1m)[0m, causing the symbol resolution failure.                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. Areas for Further Investigation                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - `ShellCodeDetector` class in full: verify whether any other references to      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `StringUtils` remain [1m([0me.g., in helper methods like `[1;35misShell[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m`[1m)[0m.                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Utility classes under `org.apache.tika.utils`:                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • `StringUtils` — understand its responsibilities and whether it’s still       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         referenced elsewhere.                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • `ProcessUtils` and `FileProcessResult` — assess if other detectors or        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m135[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mStringUtils.isBlank[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmimeString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Address the missing `StringUtils` symbol in ShellCodeDetector.java  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Locate the line:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mStringUtils.isBlank[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfileName[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return [0m[1;35misShell[0m[1;39m([0m[39misShell[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace it with an inlined null/blank check, for example:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfileName == null || [0m[1;35mfileName.isBlank[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return [0m[1;35misShell[0m[1;39m([0m[39misShell[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove the obsolete import:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - import org.apache.tika.utils.StringUtils;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify that no other references to `StringUtils` remain in the class.  If [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthere are, apply the same inlining strategy [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `s == null || [0m[1;35ms.isBlank[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Keep the processless “shebang” detection logic intact  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Do not re–introduce external process invocation. The replacement code using [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`BufferedReader` and `Files.newBufferedReader` is correct and removes the [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOS-command-injection vulnerability.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure necessary imports are present [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `java.nio.file.Path`, [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`java.io.BufferedReader`, `java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets`, [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`java.nio.file.Files`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Remove any unused imports [0m[1;39m([0m[39msuch as `FileUtils`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m if the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtemp-directory cleanup code has been deleted.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preserve existing behaviors and tests  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The only behavior change is dropping the “run the script and see if it exits [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mzero” check. All other detection logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mblank resource-name fallback via `isShell`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfilename sanitization, metadata population[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remains untouched.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Since the blank-name fallback still dispatches through `[0m[1;35misShell[0m[1;39m([0m[39misShell[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, any[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtests expecting that branch will continue to pass.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Sanity-check and compile  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After inlining the blank check and removing the unused import, rebuild [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-core`. The compilation error around `StringUtils` should be resolved.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run the full test suite to ensure no regressions.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Inlining `[0m[1;35mStringUtils.isBlank[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` fully resolves the missing‐symbol error [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout dragging back in the entire utility class.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Behavior and metadata flows remain identical to the intended patch: scripts with [0m [2m                [0m
